description:
Whaling industry 1820 and the start of the Civil War.

In the fiction Moby-dick; or The Whale, the allegorical novel about Captain Ahab's search to kill a great white whale. Captain Ahab, a fictional character, is a one-legged captain of the whaling vessel Pequod. He was monomaniacally pursuing his elusive nemesis.
